{
  "stem": "1338.3",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I think it has to do with my memory, not with my vocabulary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A water well that you pump, and so I would go out to the bucket, and I would get it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "See, the reason why I don't remember water well is because the world well doesn't apply to this subject.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyway, so I brought this water and we washed it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then since I was an electrical engineer, we had the meter outside, which was not metering the electricity but limiting it to 25 watts.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If you do more, you couldn't use it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we had one bulb for 25 watts.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's all you can use.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what I did is I had to made a short across it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I would then put the electricity, as much as I wanted it, and hide it inside.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Underneath the floor we had a little hole there which you would put food, cool, to keep it cool, I would put there a bucket of water, and I would boil the water, and my mother would mix it with the burned wheat that they gave us instead of coffee.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They gave us burnt wheat, which you couldn't eat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was bitter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we'd mixed it up, and I would bake it all night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the wire would be such that if somebody knocked on the door, my mother could pull it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Or I could pull it, and if somebody walked in to check, you could not find it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "If they found it, that would have meant, of course, immediate deportation or, equivalently, death.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyway, so that was one of the things that I ventured to do in terms of I was an electrical engin-- that was my first life-saving electrical engineering thing.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
